.TH THEMEMGR "1" "December 2025" "thememgr 202103310710-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
thememgr \- Theme manager for installing and managing Linux desktop themes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B thememgr
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR] [\fI\,THEME\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B thememgr
is a theme management system for installing, updating, and managing desktop themes from preconfigured GitHub repositories. It provides a unified interface for managing GTK themes, window manager themes, and other visual themes commonly used in Linux desktop environments.
.PP
thememgr supports installation from the thememgr organization repositories on GitHub, automatic theme cache updates, search functionality for discovering available themes, and proper theme version tracking. The tool is designed for desktop users who want consistent visual themes across multiple systems.
.PP
All themes are managed through Git repositories, making it easy to version control, update, and synchronize theme installations across different machines.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B makecache
Update system theme cache database after theme changes. This command regenerates the theme cache so newly installed themes become available to desktop environments and applications.
.TP
.B list
List all themes currently available in the thememgr repository catalog
.TP
.B search \fI\,<term>\/\fR
Search for available themes matching the specified term. Useful for finding themes by name or style.
.TP
.B available
Show all available themes from the GitHub repository. Fetches complete list from GitHub API.
.TP
.B install \fI\,<theme>\/\fR
Install a theme package from the preconfigured repository. Downloads the theme files and installs them to the appropriate system location.
.TP
.B update \fI\,[theme]\/\fR
Update theme packages. If no theme is specified, updates all installed themes. If a specific theme is provided, updates only that theme.
.TP
.B remove \fI\,<theme>\/\fR
Remove an installed theme package and its files from the system
.TP
.B download \fI\,<theme>\/\fR
Download or clone a theme repository without installing. Useful for examining themes or manual installation.
.TP
.B cron \fI\,[add|remove|run]\/\fR
Manage automatic theme updates via cron job. Add schedules periodic updates, remove cancels scheduled updates, run executes update immediately.
.TP
.B version \fI\,<theme>\/\fR
Display version information for an installed theme package
