.SH THEME STRUCTURE
Themes typically follow this directory structure:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
~/.local/share/themes/theme-name/
├── index.theme          (theme metadata)
├── gtk-2.0/            (GTK 2 theme files)
│   ├── gtkrc
│   └── assets/
├── gtk-3.0/            (GTK 3 theme files)
│   ├── gtk.css
│   ├── gtk-dark.css
│   └── assets/
├── gtk-4.0/            (GTK 4 theme files)
│   ├── gtk.css
│   ├── gtk-dark.css
│   └── assets/
├── metacity-1/         (Metacity window manager theme)
├── openbox-3/          (Openbox window manager theme)
├── xfwm4/              (Xfce window manager theme)
└── cinnamon/           (Cinnamon desktop theme)
.EE
.RE
.SH THEME CACHE
After installing or removing themes, the system theme cache may need updating:
.PP
.RS 4
# thememgr automatically updates cache when needed
.br
thememgr makecache
.RE
.PP
Desktop environments and applications may need to be restarted or refreshed to detect newly installed themes.
.SH DESKTOP INTEGRATION
Themes integrate with major Linux desktop environments:
.SS GNOME
Use GNOME Tweaks to select themes:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Open GNOME Tweaks
.IP \(bu 2
Navigate to Appearance section
.IP \(bu 2
Select GTK theme, Shell theme, Icon theme
.RE
.PP
Or use gsettings:
.RS
gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface gtk-theme 'theme-name'
.br
gsettings set org.gnome.shell.extensions.user-theme name 'theme-name'
.RE
.SS KDE Plasma
Use System Settings to select themes:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Open System Settings
.IP \(bu 2
Navigate to Appearance → Application Style
.IP \(bu 2
Select theme from list
.RE
.SS Xfce
Use Appearance settings:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Open Settings → Appearance
.IP \(bu 2
Navigate to Style tab
.IP \(bu 2
Select theme from list
.RE
.SS MATE
Use MATE Appearance Preferences:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Open System → Preferences → Appearance
.IP \(bu 2
Navigate to Theme tab
.IP \(bu 2
Select theme from list
.RE
