.SH THEME COMPONENTS
Desktop themes typically consist of several components:
.SS GTK Theme
Controls the appearance of GTK applications including:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Window decorations and borders
.IP \(bu 2
Buttons, checkboxes, and input fields
.IP \(bu 2
Scrollbars and progress bars
.IP \(bu 2
Menus and tooltips
.IP \(bu 2
Application colors and styling
.RE
.SS Window Manager Theme
Controls window decorations for specific window managers:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Title bar appearance
.IP \(bu 2
Window borders and shadows
.IP \(bu 2
Close, minimize, maximize buttons
.IP \(bu 2
Active/inactive window states
.RE
.SS Shell Theme
Desktop environment specific shell themes:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Panel/taskbar appearance
.IP \(bu 2
System tray styling
.IP \(bu 2
Desktop background integration
.IP \(bu 2
Notification styling
.RE
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Theme installations are managed through preconfigured GitHub repositories under the thememgr organization
.IP \(bu 2
Each theme package includes GTK 2/3/4 themes, window manager themes, and shell themes as applicable
.IP \(bu 2
Themes are installed to user directories by default (~/.local/share/themes)
.IP \(bu 2
System-wide installation may require root privileges
.IP \(bu 2
Theme cache is automatically updated after installation when using makecache
.IP \(bu 2
Installed themes are tracked in ~/.local/share/CasjaysDev/apps/thememgr/
.IP \(bu 2
Desktop notifications can be disabled by setting THEMEMGR_NOTIFY_ENABLED=no
.IP \(bu 2
Most desktop environments require logout/login or restart to fully apply new themes
.IP \(bu 2
Some applications may require restart to detect newly installed themes
.IP \(bu 2
Dark theme variants often have "-Dark" suffix in their names
.SH THEME DEVELOPMENT
Themes can be customized by editing CSS files in the theme directory. GTK 3 and GTK 4 themes use CSS for styling, making them relatively easy to modify.
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
# Edit GTK 3 theme
$EDITOR ~/.local/share/themes/theme-name/gtk-3.0/gtk.css

# Edit GTK 4 theme
$EDITOR ~/.local/share/themes/theme-name/gtk-4.0/gtk.css
.EE
.RE
